Class BinderFactorySupport

All Implemented Interfaces:
BinderFactory, Component, GenericStateModel
Direct Known Subclasses:
ServiceFilter
public abstract class BinderFactorySupport
extends GenericStateModelAdapter
implements BinderFactory

Implement the basics of a BinderFactory. A full implementation will at least implement the getBinderClass() method and may override getBinder. We expect many BinderFactory implementations to not use this base class at all and write full implementations themselves.

The default implementation does not implement setParameter or request any services.

getBinderClass

protected java.lang.Class getBinderClass(java.lang.Object child)
Override to choose the class of the Binder to use. This method should return null if the child is not bindable with this Factory. The default implementation returns null.

bindChild

protected Binder bindChild(java.lang.Class binderClass,
                           java.lang.Object child)
Bind the Child component.

The child component will already have been instantiated and any parameter has been set. Depending on the ComponentFactory (or other constructor/initializer methods) used, there may have been additional initialization performed.

Generally all this method does is construct a new instance of bindingSite for use with the child component. Various implementations may do additional Binder initialization such as starting a thread, instructing the binder to provide additional services, etc. By default, it does the equivalent of return new binderClass(ContainerAPI,child);

Returns:
A Binder instance of class bindingSite which is binding the child component or null.
